HEADWORD: marshy
<hw>marsh"y</hw> <pr>(m⟦aum⟧rsh"⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[E.
<er>Marsh</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Resembling a marsh; wet; boggy; fenny.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Pertaining to, or produced in, marshes; <as>as, a
<ex>marshy</ex> weed</as>.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

